author: Ashleigh Davis For Daily Mail Australia
title: Perth man contorts body through the top of a bike rack
text:
Have you ever pushed your flexibility to the absolute limits, just to see how far your body can bend?
A Perth man did exactly that when he twisted his body to fit through the space at the top of a bicycle rack.
The video, uploaded by Frisk Small Bar - a bar in the Perth suburb of Northbridge, shows 'Bret' standing next to a traffic light before he shimmies towards the camera.
Dressed in a shirt, shorts and a pair of trainers, he starts the challenge by bending to one side and putting his left leg through the small space.
Supporting himself with one hand on the top of the bike rack and the other on the ground, he makes sure his appendage is tucked through before he bends in half to manoeuvre his upper body through the opening.
A Perth man has contorted his body to fit through a tiny opening at the top of a single bike rack. He started by putting his left leg through (left), followed by his upper torso (right)
Keeping his right leg on one side, he then pulls the rest of his body through the small opening, followed by his leg.
As he is attempting the flexible feat, the woman filming his heard cackling with laughter.
After he makes it through to the other side, he gives a high kick to celebrate the victory and runs off into the dark with his arms outstretched.
He then pulled his right leg through the space (left) and did a high kick and jump to celebrate the victory of reaching the other side (right)
